name: ConditionalFormatIconCriterion
description: Represents an Icon Criterion which contains a type, value, an Operator, and an optional custom icon, if not using an iconset.

properties.name: type
properties.description: What the icon conditional formula should be based on.

properties.name: formula
properties.description: A number, a formula, or null (if Type is LowestValue, HighestValue, or Automatic).

properties.name: operator
properties.description: GreaterThan or GreaterThanOrEqual for each of the rule type for the Icon conditional format.

properties.name: customIcon
properties.description: An icon type, where one can select a specific icon for this criterion.

methods.name: load
methods.description: Fills the proxy object created in JavaScript layer with property and object values specified in the parameter.

parameters.name: param
parameters.description: Accepts parameter and relationship names as delimited string or an array. Or, provide [loadOption](loadoption.md) object.
